ed to pursue graduate studies or move forward into key leadership roles in our country as civilians or military officers  A liberal arts degree from VMI has opened doors for business leaders  civil servants  and diplomats  as well as authors  actors  and scholars  A cadet may be awarded the degree of Bachelor of Arts with a major in English  history or modern languages and cultures  All three departments also offer minors and or concentrations  Departments English  Rhetoric    Humanistic Studies History Modern Languages   Cultures VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu 